# Cosmo runs in DEMO MODE by default — every key in this file is optional.
# `npm run dev` boots clean with NOTHING set: auth is mocked to a single demo
# user, Supabase calls short-circuit to canned data, and Stripe / Resend /
# Inngest live behind the same "configured?" gate. See README.md for details.
#
# Flip a service to live by uncommenting the matching keys below and
# restarting the dev server. The runtime detects the change automatically
# (no code edits needed).

# --- Vercel AI Gateway (recommended for the demo) ---------------------------
# The chat + completion endpoints route through Vercel's AI Gateway when this
# key is set. Without it (and without OPENAI_API_KEY), the chat surface still
# loads but every model call returns "No AI provider configured."
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=

# Direct OpenAI fallback — used only when AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY is missing.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key

# --- Supabase (auth + DB) ---------------------------------------------------
# Leave all three blank to stay in demo mode (mock auth, in-memory chats, no
# persistence across restarts). Set all three to wire a real Supabase project.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# --- Inngest (job queue) ---------------------------------------------------
# Optional — `npm run dev` boots the local Inngest CLI without these.
# INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=
# INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=

# --- Resend (transactional email) ------------------------------------------
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# RESEND_FROM="Cosmo <hello@yourdomain.com>"
# RESEND_ALERT_FROM="Cosmo Alerts <alerts@yourdomain.com>"
# RESEND_ALERT_TO=
# # Set to "1" in dev to actually send; default no-ops.
# RESEND_ALLOW_SEND=

# --- Stripe (billing) ------------------------------------------------------
# Stub-by-default — leave blank to render the billing chrome without any keys.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# STRIPE_PRICE_ID=
